items.title: German inflation dips to cooler-than-expected 1.8% in July
items.description: Economists polled by Reuters had expected inflation to ease to 1.9%.

items.title: The Fed is unlikely to cut rates Wednesday, but this meeting is packed with intrigue
items.description: Considering nothing is likely to happen when it comes to major policy decisions, the meeting promises several fascinating subplots.

items.title: Private company hiring bounced back with a 104,000 increase in July, ADP says
items.description: Payrolls rose by a seasonally adjusted 104,000 for the month, reversing a loss of 23,000 in June.

items.title: U.S. economy grew at a 3% rate in Q2, a better-than-expected pace even as Trump's tariffs hit
items.description: Gross domestic product was expected to grow at a 2.3% annualized pace in the second quarter, according to the consensus estimate.

items.title: Companies from Stanley Black & Decker to Conagra are saying tariffs will cost them hundreds of millions
items.description: Businesses in a range of industries have raced to figure out how to handle rising costs in the middle of a shakeup in global trade policy.
